<div style="font-size:25px; margin-left: 10px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 5px; text-align:left;">'''Survival Difficulty: Class 5E - Environmental'''</div></div></div>
<div style="font-size:20px; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px; text-align:left;">'''》Exceedingly Unsafe'''</div>
<div style="font-size:20px; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 8px; text-align:left;">'''》Stabilized Structure'''</div>
<div style="font-size:20px; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 8px; text-align:left;">'''》Extremely Harsh Environment'''</div>


<div class="header">Description</div>
[[File:Iceland.png|600px|center|link=]]
<div style="margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px;">
'''Level 908''' serves as a perilous level constituting a barren, frozen ocean, characterized by its gargantuan icebergs. Said icebergs feature a multitude of towering spikes protruding from them in a crystalline manner. Multiple stars dot the level's eternal night sky, oftentimes brighter than stars observed from [[The Frontrooms|Earth]]. Occasionally, a cyan celestial object rises to outshine these stars for a few hours. Strangely, '''Level 908'''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s ocean remains liquid, despite the temperatures being far below freezing. Thanks to its bitingly gelid environment, inadequately-equipped wanderers will last up to 20 minutes before their frosty demise.

The ice of '''Level 908''' has a slicked surface, making wanderers slip and fall when not exercising caution with their movement. This may lead to fatal injuries, where the ice spikes may viscerally impale a careless wanderer. If not, one may hit their head on the hard ice, instantly knocking one unconscious. Individuals left unconscious for one to two minutes, which includes merely falling asleep, will die. Slipping on the ice may also send one to the algid ocean, which would swiftly kill those thanks to various factors.

Any non-living biomatter, such as corpses and foodstuffs, will instantaneously freeze. The resulting frozen mass is brittle, with the formations crumbling into a collection of ice shards and fleshy mist on a single punch. Inhaling the mist often kills one within a few minutes, as they haplessly watch themselves freeze alive. The same fate befalls those who attempt to consume and swallow any frozen foods. [[Object 1|Almond Water]] is the only consumable that doesn't freeze and remains safe for consumption within '''Level 908'''. In addition to this, Almond Water is able to melt the level's ice, allowing for safe consumption. Ingesting water native to the level, when warm, is thought to remedy the level's deathly chill, allowing for prolonged survival even when unprepared. 

'''Level 908''' hinders any electronics brought in and dampens their effectiveness or outright permanently destroys them. Modern technology such as phones are most vulnerable, with phones having unresponsive screens, slowed performance, failure to activate, and more. Older technology, such as certain radios and walkie-talkies fare better in the level, often working as intended for multiple minutes until some minute malfunctions are present, though these persist even upon leaving '''Level 908'''. Any disruptions to electronics caused by the level are deemed irreparable, at least given the technological capabilities of Backrooms societies.

Notwithstanding its fatal perils, the landscape and atmosphere of '''Level 908''' is known to captivate sensations of wonder among those who stumble upon it. Wanderers often feel enchanted by the stupendous spiked icebergs, the night sky, all illuminated by the faint cyan sun as its light dances through the majestic ice spikes. Taking in the sights of '''Level 908''' delays the detrimental impact the level has on one, yet it might distract them from leaving, and thus succumbing to an algid death.
</div>
