<center>"Hidden Beauty Within the Ice"</center><br><br><br>When I arrived in the world of ice, I could not believe my eyes. In my line of vision were magnificent iceforms reaching towards the sky. The beautiful moon loomed above, lightly shining upon the level. The sea glittered and reflected off a deep, dark blue. Such great sites were rare in the Backrooms, and I intend to cherish this moment forever. I sat down and stared into the horizon. The endless icescape stared back at me. I breathed in the cold air, as tranquility gradually filled me with a warmness that remains unreplicated.<br><br>As I continue my journeys through the level, I found nothing but peace. The frost held me to the ground, and wistfulness wrapped around me as I recall the days of reality. But maybe this hellscape wasn't so bad. In the journey of bitterness comes along sweet spots. These are the moments that you have to latch onto, and get the best out of. If you let it pass quickly, the bitterness returns, and life snaps you back.<br><br>In the blink of an eye, a heavenly sight can pass by without you knowing. With a photo, things will last eternally. I leave my pen, and I provide you, the reader, with the image below. Farewell, for now.<br><br>-Phoebe V. Coppes
