<div class="header">Entrances and Exits</div><br>
<div style="text-align:left;">
<big><big>Entrances</big></big>
*Noclipping through a slab of ice at least the size of an adult human will lead one here from [[Level 100]];
*Falling asleep on [[Level 205]] will lead one here;
*Noclipping through a puddle in [[Level 186]] will lead one here;
*Noclipping within a crevasse in [[Level 202]] will lead one here;
*A sinkhole in [[Level 907]] will lead one here;
*Any noclipping in [[Level 410]] will lead one here;
*Pressing a cyan button sporting a snowflake symbol in an [[Object 34|Elevator]];
*Occasionally, reaching the surface of [[Level 857]] will lead here;
*At [[Level 809]]'s factory, finding a freezer room and activating their cooling systems and remaining inside will cause the individual to lose consciousness within a short period, after which they will awaken in here;
*Noclipping through a freezer in [[Level 711]] will lead here; and
*A blue door labeled with either an ice symbol, a snowflake symbol, or glacier symbol will lead here.
<big><big>Exits</big></big>
*The aforementioned door will persist for 45 seconds after entry, after which it will vanish into a cold mist. Taking this door mostly leads one back to their previous level, but it rarely leads to other, randomized levels;
*Diving into the water and resurfacing may rarely lead to [[Level 102]];
*Noclipping through an iceberg may lead to [[Level 269]];
*Noclipping through the water may lead to [[Level 330]];
*Running and tripping may lead to [[Level 822]]; and
*A tunnel in an iceberg leads to [[Level 909]].
</div></div>

